# FlowForge

## Overview

FlowForge is a multi-tenant SaaS platform that enables teams to define, execute, and manage AI-powered workflows through an asynchronous, event-driven architecture.

It is designed for teams that need reliable AI automation with structured execution, background processing, and secure access control across shared workspaces.

---

## Goals

1. Provide a scalable workflow execution system powered by asynchronous job processing.
2. Enforce strict multi-tenant isolation with role-based access control across all resources.
3. Ensure reliable execution of AI tasks through queue-based architecture and worker separation.
4. Support subscription-based monetization using Stripe billing.
5. Provide real-time visibility into workflow execution state.

---

## Core User Flow

1. User signs up and authenticates via Auth.js.
2. User creates or joins a workspace (multi-tenant boundary).
3. User defines an AI workflow (prompt + input structure).
4. User triggers workflow execution.
5. System enqueues job into Redis (BullMQ queue).
6. Worker processes job asynchronously using OpenAI API.
7. Execution result is stored in PostgreSQL.
8. Real-time update is pushed to client (status + output).
9. User views execution history and results.

---

## Features

### Authentication & Workspaces

- Secure session-based authentication
- Multi-tenant workspace creation and membership system
- Role-based access control (Owner, Admin, Member)

---

### AI Workflow Engine

- Create reusable AI workflows using structured prompts
- Execute workflows asynchronously via job queue system
- Store execution history and outputs

---

### Job Queue System

- Redis + BullMQ-based background processing
- Decoupled execution from API lifecycle
- Retry handling and failure tracking

---

### Billing System

- Stripe subscription integration
- Plan-based access control
- Webhook-driven billing state updates

---

### Realtime Execution Tracking

- Live workflow execution updates
- Status tracking (queued, running, completed, failed)

---

### API Access Layer

- API key-based authentication for external usage
- Rate limiting per workspace and plan

---

## Scope

### In Scope

- Multi-tenant SaaS architecture
- AI workflow creation and execution system
- Background job processing with Redis queues
- Role-based access control system
- Stripe subscription billing
- Execution tracking and history
- API key access layer

---

### Out of Scope

- Real-time collaboration editing (Google Docs-style)
- Advanced AI agent orchestration systems
- Multi-region infrastructure deployment
- Mobile application
- Offline execution support

---

## Success Criteria

1. A user can create a workspace, define a workflow, and execute it end-to-end successfully.
2. All workflow executions are processed asynchronously via queue workers without blocking API routes.
3. Workspace isolation is strictly enforced across all database queries.
4. Subscription plans correctly restrict feature access via Stripe billing state.
5. Workflow execution results are stored, retrievable, and tracked with status history.